Racking my brain this offseason for budgeting to get this car back on the road. I think I’ll do it in stages because it won’t be cheap.

Bought a MIG welder to fix some sheet metal on the front end and I also need to patch a spot on the WRX.

@r4ted_m and I have been trying to find opportunities on the weekends to get some fresh air in the mountains. Between work, side projects, and exercise; we’43 juggling all the fun stuff.

Thanks @therestingmitchface for posting some throwbacks, gives me some motivation to get the hatch running again. I just have a bunch of ideas written down. Now I just need to push forward and execute the plans.

Happy Valentines Suzie! Thanks for always being my adventure partner and soulmate! Thank you for always being supportive of all the different hobbies we have! Thank you for the Valentines cake 🥹 @kitassweettreats @initialderp you the best! 2023 is just getting started!

it runs!
 need to get a tune and fix rear camber/alignment

Need to fix my camber in the rear, ordered Limit Break RLCAs, bothered @partsshopmax asking for 5x114.3 FRS Hubs, dug out the fiberglass, mounted my bent pop up to see how well I did fixing the corner.

Now I’m remembering all the small things I need to do to this car before I can drive it again and since I moved in, I’m now realizing I’m missing random parts. 😅 

Oh yeah… have to put the other motor on the engine stand. 🥲

Finally got to drive the 240 around tonight and fill up 12 gallons of 92 octane.

Resealed the motor, tossed in a new flywheel, white bunny stage 3 clutch, new motor mounts. After breaking a traction rod, I needed to throw in a new z33 axle, and ordered fresh new @partsshopmax rear arms. 

Somethings still going on with the front suspension that I need to figure out, it still feels like the knuckle is shifting or the alignment is off? Under braking the front wheels start to obnoxiously shake!!!

Despite the rear knuckle breaking, the car did phenomenal at Bash. Saturday after fixing the knuckle, I got a a ton of laps in the afternoon and for night driving. Sunday, I got to hotlap the track early in the morning and killed a couple of pairs of tires. Got home before the sun went down, washed the car. Now it’s time to go over the car for some updates. Thanks @valinotirenw @cameronmooredrift for motivating me to come out and drive!
